<section class="sd-section"><h2>How a core return works</h2><p>Many remanufactured and high-performance parts begin as used components removed from vehicles. A CORE (Cash On Return) charge encourages the return of a reusable component for remanufacturing.</p><p>For eligible purchases, you can pay the core charge and request a refund after an acceptable core is returned within the applicable period. Alternatively, you may send the core first and the replacement part ships after the core is received and accepted. Return freight is generally the customer&rsquo;s responsibility, though reduced-cost prepaid shipping may be available for selected products.</p></section>
<section class="sd-section"><h2>Prepare the core</h2><ol class="sd2-core__steps"><li><span>01</span><div><strong>Remove fittings</strong><p>Remove fittings and transferable hardware from the old unit unless the product-specific instructions say otherwise.</p></div></li><li><span>02</span><div><strong>Drain fluids</strong><p>Drain fuel and oil, then contain any residue so it cannot escape the packaging and delay carrier handling.</p></div></li><li><span>03</span><div><strong>Include the form</strong><p>Place the completed Core Return Form inside the box and reuse the original box and protective packaging when possible.</p></div></li></ol><a class="sd2-cp__button sd2-cp__button--primary" target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="/pdfs_forms/Core%20Return%20Form.pdf">Download Core Return Form</a></section>
<section class="sd-section"><h2>Package it correctly</h2><div class="sd2-core__compare"><figure><mvt:item name="readytheme" param="image( 'correctly-packaged-core' )" /><figcaption><strong>Correct</strong><ul><li>Original box and protective material reused</li><li>No fluid residue leaking through the carton</li><li>Core Return Form included and accessible</li></ul></figcaption></figure><figure><mvt:item name="readytheme" param="image( 'incorrectly-packaged-core' )" /><figcaption><strong>Incorrect</strong><ul><li>Insufficient protection around the core</li><li>Fuel or oil residue escaping the package</li><li>Core Return Form missing</li></ul></figcaption></figure></div></section>
<section class="sd-section"><h2>Core credit timing</h2><div class="sd2-core__credit"><article><span>Full credit</span><p>Core received within 60 days in acceptable condition. Shipping damage remains the responsibility of the customer and carrier.</p></article><article><span>Half credit</span><p>Core received between 60 and 180 days after purchase, or with slight housing damage, subject to inspection.</p></article><article><span>No credit</span><p>Core is rusted, corroded, fire-damaged, seized or received after 180 days.</p></article></div><p>Keep tracking information until the refund is received. Allow up to two weeks after acceptance for processing; approved refunds return to the original payment method.</p></section>
<section class="sd-section"><h2>Common questions</h2><div class="sd2-blue__faq"><details><summary>What if another manufacturer made the part?</summary><p>Follow the manufacturer&rsquo;s return instructions included with the replacement. The core must be returned to that manufacturer, whose inspection determines acceptance. Sinister Diesel processes the refund after receiving the manufacturer&rsquo;s approval.</p></details><details><summary>What if I send the core first?</summary><p>Sinister Diesel sends a Core Return email with the form and instructions. The replacement ships after the core is received, inspected and accepted.</p></details></div></section>
